NFPRE0 is the name of the user's initial pressure function
             
This user's function compute the value of the initial pressure

- at time t, 

- at point X,Y,Z;

- for the object of type number NuTypePLS : (3:SURFACE, 2:LINE, 1:POINT)

- with the number in this directory NuPLS of this PLS

In fact, the function nuobjt( TypeName of PLSVO, Name PLSVO ) gives the number of the PLSVO in the
directory from its name;

must have all the parameters in this order:

InitialPressure( t, X,Y,Z, NuTypePLS, NuPLS ) 

All these parameters are initialized at the function call during the execution.
They may be used or not, in the body of the function to compute the value of a force components.
          
EXAMPLE : 
 2; 4;  { initial pressure }
 -1;    { InitialPressure function }
 DefFunc InitialPressure( t, x,y,z, NuTypePLS, boundary );
 InitialPressure=0;
 if  boundary=nuobjt( 'line' , 'wall' )
 then 
   InitialPressure=1.45;
 else
   if  boundary=nuobjt( 'surface' , 'sphere' )
   then 
     InitialPressure=-1.75;
   endif;   
 endif;
 EndFunc;
 initialpressure;      { Do not FORGET to give the name of the function! }
